   It's not that there is not enough money in the health-care system;
it's that it is going to all the wrong places. HMOs are making a
killing, while the county system is hemorrhaging.

   In Los Angeles County, the number of listings in May dropped 39%
from a year earlier, while Orange County's fell by nearly a third,
according to the California Assn. of Realtors.
